  <bioghist id="aspace_4c26f2b89ad5e676421414f18a53dc89">
    <head>History</head>
<p>The International Union of United Brewery, Flour, Cereal, Soft Drink and Distillery Workers of America, Local 267 in Logansport, Pennsylvania, began as United Distillery Workers of North America, Local 942 at Logansport Distilling Company, Inc.  In 1948, Local 942 renegotiated its agreement to create Local 267 Distillery Workers.  Both locals had participated in the United Brewery Workers Pennsylvania Council, which lobbied for the interests of brewery and distillery workers, during their existence.  The International Union of United Brewery, Flour, Cereal, Soft Drink and Distillery Workers of America merged with the Teamsters in 1973 after a lengthy battle over membership disputes.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_9246f17f7057bd7236ad8b0fe47e4fa8">
    <head>Scope and Content Notes</head>
<p>This collection includes information from 1936 to 1959 regarding both United Distillery Workers of North America, Local 942, and International Union of United Brewery, Flour, Cereal, Soft Drink and Distillery Workers of America, Local 267.  Correspondence and contracts are present, as well as meeting minutes.  Also included are union seniority lists, constitution and by-laws, and check books.  One item of note is the original certificate of affiliation between the United Distillery Workers and the Congress of Industrial Organizations from 1939.</p>  </scopecontent>
